# Tool Selection Framework

The AI must intentionally select the best combination of:

- Model
- MCP servers
- Rules
- Skills
- Agents
- Templates
- Workflows

Do not use every available tool.

Load only what improves the current task.

---

# General Principles

Always prefer:

- Accuracy
- Maintainability
- Minimal context
- Lowest reasonable cost
- Reproducibility

Avoid unnecessary tool usage.

---

# Model Selection

Choose the model according to the task.

## Architecture

Preferred characteristics:

- Deep reasoning
- Long context
- Design analysis

Examples:

- Claude Opus
- GPT reasoning models
- Other architecture-focused models

---

## Implementation

Preferred characteristics:

- Fast coding
- Predictable edits
- High implementation speed

Examples:

- GPT
- Composer 2.5
- Claude Sonnet

---

## Large Refactoring

Prefer models with:

- Long context
- Strong reasoning
- Codebase understanding

---

## Documentation

Prefer models with:

- Strong writing
- Good summarization
- Consistency

---

## Research

When current information is required:

Prefer:

- Context7
- Official documentation
- Web search

Never rely only on model memory.

---

# MCP Selection

Enable only required MCP servers.

---

## Filesystem MCP

Use when:

- Reading project files
- Refactoring
- Searching code
- Updating documentation

---

## GitHub MCP

Use when:

- Reviewing Pull Requests
- Creating Issues
- Reading Discussions
- Working with branches
- Reviewing commits

---

## Docker MCP

Use when:

- Containers
- Docker Compose
- Images
- Networks
- Local infrastructure

---

## PostgreSQL MCP

Use when:

- Schema inspection
- SQL analysis
- Migrations
- Performance analysis

Never use Production databases without approval.

---

## Context7 MCP

Always prefer Context7 before guessing:

- Library APIs
- Framework behavior
- Official documentation
- Version-specific features

---

## Playwright MCP

Use for:

- End-to-end testing
- UI validation
- Checkout testing
- Authentication flows
- Regression testing

Do not use for static code analysis.

---

## OpenAPI MCP

Use when:

- Designing APIs
- Reviewing APIs
- Generating clients
- Validating contracts

---

## Memory MCP

Use before:

- Creating conventions
- Making architecture decisions
- Introducing patterns
- Starting large refactoring

Check existing project memory first.

---

## Fetch MCP

Use when:

- Reading external documentation
- Reading articles
- Importing reference material

---

## Figma MCP

Use only when:

- UI design exists
- Components are derived from design
- Tokens need synchronization

---

## shadcn/ui MCP

Use for:

- Component selection
- Component generation
- UI consistency
- Registry lookup

Do not recreate existing components.

---

## Sentry MCP

Use when:

- Debugging production issues
- Stack traces
- Runtime exceptions
- Error investigation

---

# Rule Selection

Load only Rules related to the task.

Never load unrelated Rules.

---

# Skill Selection

Use Skills only when they improve execution.

Avoid overlapping Skills.

Prefer one specialized Skill over multiple generic Skills.

---

# Agent Selection

Activate only specialists required.

Examples:

Architecture

→ Enterprise Architect

Backend

→ Backend Engineer

Frontend

→ Frontend Engineer

Database

→ Database Engineer

Security

→ Security Engineer

Performance

→ Performance Engineer

QA

→ QA Engineer

SEO

→ SEO Specialist

---

# Context Optimization

Always minimize context.

Use:

- fewer Rules
- fewer Skills
- fewer Agents
- fewer MCP servers

while maintaining solution quality.

---

# Cost Optimization

Prefer the least expensive solution that still provides the required quality.

Escalate to more capable models only when necessary.

---

# Escalation Rules

Escalate to stronger models when:

- architecture changes
- complex debugging
- ambiguous requirements
- large refactoring
- critical business logic
- security review

---

# Validation

Before implementation verify:

✓ Correct model selected

✓ Correct MCP enabled

✓ Correct Rules loaded

✓ Correct Skills loaded

✓ Correct Agents activated

✓ Correct workflow selected

Only then begin implementation.